SIMPLE: mortality
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mortality
<hw>Mor*tal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mortalitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>mortalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition or quality of being mortal; subjection to
death or to the necessity of dying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When I saw her die,⟦br⟧
I then did think on your <qex>mortality</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Carew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 946 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Human life; the life of a mortal being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From this instant⟦br⟧
There 's nothing serious in <qex>mortality</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Those who are, or that which is, mortal; the human
race; humanity; human nature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take these tears, <qex>mortality's</qex> relief.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Death; destruction.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The whole sum or number of deaths in a given time or
a given community; also, the proportion of deaths to population, or to a
specific number of the population; death rate; <as>as, a time of great,
or low, <ex>mortality</ex>; the <ex>mortality</ex> among the settlers
was alarming.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bill of mortality</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Bill</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Law of mortality</b></col>, <cd>a
mathematical relation between the numbers living at different ages, so
that from a given large number of persons alive at one age, it can be
computed what number are likely to survive a given number of years.</cd>
-- <col><b>Table of mortality</b></col>, <cd>a table exhibiting the
average relative number of persons who survive, or who have died, at the
end of each year of life, out of a given number supposed to have been
born at the same time.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mortalize</ent>⟦br⟧
